FBIS3-43892 "drafr012_b_94004" FBIS-AFR-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 EAST AFRICA Uganda Foreign Minister in Talks With Indian Official EA1901113594 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1400 GMT 18 Jan 94 EA1901113594 Kampala Radio Uganda Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] India has expressed interest to invest in Uganda in the fields of agriculture, small-scale industries, and hydroelectric power generation. This was revealed by the secretary in the Indian Ministry of External Affairs, Mr. (Salman Haydar), when he paid a courtesy call on the second deputy prime minister and minister of foreign affairs, Mr. Paul Kawanga Ssemogerere, at his office in Kampala. [passage omitted]
